Dual-loop Self-regulating Ultracompact TEG

A more complex Thermo-Electric Generator design that utilizes a pneumatic valve to handle automatic burn chamber venting and easy throttle changes. This design uses two separate loops to better retain heat. This method sees a doubling of effective power compared to a single regenerative cooling loop design.

Design by ArtisticRoomba (Roomba Angle).
120 kPa is good for most stations. You can adjust the pressure of this pump to increase or decrease the power output.

For working gasses:
Plasma > Water Vapor > CO2 > Oxygen/Nitrogen

Use for balancing the contents of both loops and for clearing pressure jams.

Open when connecting the tank, close before operation.
Build the passive vents and air injector first before building the radiators!
